title: The ?MODULE macro returns the current module's name.
pid: f92bc235-73f0-46f8-b34f-57f6002878a7
body: |2-
  It's useful, e.g., for writing a helper function in module M
  that spawns another function also defined in module M:

  start(FoodList) ->
      spawn( ?MODULE,
   	  fridge2,
   	  [FoodList] ).
misc:
- Had_ID_Before_Import
